<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB03911</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING REPUBLIC ACT NO. 8972, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE SOLO PARENTS' WELFARE ACT OF 2010, PROVIDING FOR ADDITIONAL BENEFITS ON BASIC COMMODITIES, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to amend the existing law to address the financial concerns of solo parents by providing
them additional support and benefits which include:

a) 10% discount - clothing/clothing materials for the child 0 - 2 y.o.;
b) 15% discount - baby's milk, food/food supplements;
c) 15% discount - medicines/medical supplements/supplies for the child;
d) Basic personal exemption from individual income tax.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>LEGARDA, LOREN</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-08-14</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Savellano (000 2020-02-06)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON REVISION OF LAWS ON 2019-08-27</td></tr></table>